text.tspan: The Hook is a live updated coat rack that uses a series of LED grids to
display the weather over the item of clothing to wear on each day. You
customise what hook holds what item of clothing via a browser based
GUI screen which then syncs with a Raspberry Pi built to the device. The
Raspberry PI gets data from the weather office and gets the Geo location
from the browser and then combines that data to then send a signal to
show a weather animation over the hook which holds the item of clothing
that you should wear that day, the GUI screen is useful because it means
you can configure the number of hooks you want live and what you want
on each hook to avoid having to have a winter coat on a hook during the
Best of all the case is made of LEGO!!!

flowRoot.flowPara: The insides contain a raspberry pi that acts as both a Wi-Fi hotspot and a controller for the LEDs which
